			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I've noticed one flaw: let's say I drop something (I drop something worthless that makes me look like a bag), and I Minor Illusion, and look at myself, I look like the bag. If I stay in the same zone, and run over to a tree, cast the spell, I see myself as a bag, but everyone else sees me as a tree. <BR>
<BR>
What's the problem with this? I play on a PvP server. Once, I Illusioned myself to look like a campfire, and I looked like a campfire. Later, in a dangerous cave, I dropped something, Illusioned, and thought I looked like a bag...I was still the campfire, though when I looked at myself I still saw the bag...<BR>
PKers saw me right away and killed me. <BR>
NPCs don't seem to mind, and no, they don't seem to attack at all, provided you're an inanimate object, but others players can still hit you.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
