	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Somebody remembers seeing walls and pyramid illusions?  What that was is during beta (and possibly even early in EQ's release als), Minor Illusion duplicated a wider range of items.  In Beta 4, I remember becoming a goblin/orc hut, a large totem pole (like the one outside Crushbone), and the city walls of Felwithe.  Back in those days, you could also move as the item also.  A floating teacup or vase running along was always entertaining.<BR>
<BR>
Now adays, Minor Illusion only does relatively small items.  There was never a Greater Illusion spell that I was aware of, although I believe it's existance was debated amongst the Enchanter community throughout Phase 4.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
