	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				One great use for this spell is to get the mana spells (crystalize, thicken, et al).  The brownies are not very friendly (the sellers of the first two mana spells).  In fact, they just might bite your knee caps off.  Even with Alliance, they will barely tolerate you... and certainly rarely sell to you.  But, cast this in front of a merchant and your faction becomes 0.  Now you can buy those spells from the brownies.  Considering the poor prices of the South Ro Orc and Eurodite, try being a campfire and trading.  Maybe this won't help you in town, but it does help where they tell you to hit the door.  And, surprisingly, if you do this in front of a merchant, you can still trade with that merchant without losing form.  This is great for selling at the North Ro Gypsy camp (those darn Griffons and Giants make little noise sneaking up on you).<BR>
Remember... the enchanter is quite flexible.  Look for new ways to use old spells... make the wizzies jealous!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
