	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Firstly, let me say that I disagree with the previous poster wholeheartedly.  Enchanters can: make magical items, do almost any quest via illusion/faction spells, control the flow of monsters, summon pets (medium sucky pets, but still handy, and we can buff 'em), cast a few very nice DD spells (43 points per pop at 8th), make monsters do what we want, camp wherever we want in (almost) complete safety, _and_ we're a lot of fun for the special effects/wow factor.  After 8th level, I expect to end up with massive amounts of money from quests (greater light stone and, eventually, stein come to mind) and from selling magic items.<BR>
<BR>
As an example, here are a few things I've noted about minor illusion:<BR>
I have never had a monster target me for aggression while minor illusioned without me attacking him first.  This includes skeletons, but I imagine I've just been lucky in that respect.  You can run around invis, cast minor illusion to break the invis (leaving you vulnerable for about 2 sec), then loot your corpse in a dangerous place or deal with merchants in safety.  You can then cast any non-aggresive spell (when solo, I almost always buff &amp; summon pet in illusioned form).  This means you can go back invis without breaking minor illusion, then turn it off.  Or you can gate straight home after dealing with an evil merchant without becoming vulnerable again!  You also, as a side note, get infravision while minor illusioned (although of course you can't move).  This is a great spell, and I anticipate using it at least for soloing throughout my career as an enchanter.<BR>
<BR>
Tobas of Qeynos, Innoruk server
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
